cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI

The paper proposes a method for generating depth maps from holoscopic 3D images, which involves computer vision techniques such as disparity calculation, cost aggregation, and graph cut. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions applications in robotics (cs.RO), AR/VR (cs.MM), and entertainment (cs.GR), indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant. Additionally, the use of sub-pixel accuracy and winner takes all algorithm suggests a focus on optimization and efficiency, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
